article.headline: Montana State 76, Idaho State 71
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Calvin Ento had 17 points as Montana State beat Idaho State 76-71 Thursday night. The Bobcats (13-10, 5-5 Big Sky) led the Bengals (10-14, 5-4) by 23 points at 52-29 with 19:24 left in the game but with 3:04 to go only had a two-point lead at 69-67. Then MSU's Nick Dissly banked in a 3-point shot from the left side and ISU never got closer then three points the rest of the way. In the first half, Montana State hit eight 3-pointers and they finished with 10 for the game. Going in, the Bobcats were the last in the conference in that category. Jason Erickson, who fouled out with 6:45 to go, had 14 points and Danny Faaborg added 12, including going 4-for-9 on 3-pointers. Idaho State was led by Marquis Poole with 31 points on 12-of-18 shooting.
